    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\nSetting a color via `-Q...+p<color>` also paints the vector stem. It could be intended, but I find no mention of this behaviour in the [documentation for `+p`](https://docs.generic-mapping-tools.org/latest/grdvector.html#vector-attributes). Perhaps the less surprising behaviour would be to preserve the `-W` defaults as per the documentation (`[Default: width = default, color = black, style = solid]`).\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/sh\r\n\r\ngmt begin arrow_head_pen\r\n    gmt grdmath -R-2/2/-2/2 -I0.1 X Y R2 NEG EXP X MUL = z.nc\r\n    gmt grdmath z.nc DDX = dzdx.nc\r\n    gmt grdmath z.nc DDY = dzdy.nc\r\n    gmt grdvector dzdx.nc dzdy.nc -JX12c/0 -Baf -BWSen -I0.3 -Q0.4+e+n0.4+p1,red+h0 -Ggreen\r\ngmt end show\r\nrm z.nc dzdx.nc dzdy.nc\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo reset the stem color, it is necessary to append `-Wblack` to the grdvector call.\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* Operating system: Linux x86_64 5.14.16-arch1-1 with GCC 11.1.0\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`): 6.2.0\r\n",
